 Career History



Chief Technology Officer & Head, Product

                                    2012 - Current                


Mashable, Inc.


                  Mashable, Inc.  operates a global, multi-platform media and entertainment company. It videos, social media, technology, business, entertainment, world news, lifestyle channels.  The company was founded by Peter Cashmore in 2005 and is headquartered in New York, NY.                




Vice President-Product & Technology

                                    2008 - 2010                


NBCUniversal Media LLC


                  NBCUniversal Media LLC owns and operates news and entertainment television networks. Its businesses cover broadcasting, sports, television series, movies, fashion programs, and theatrical, and non-theatrical filmed entertainment contents. The company was founded on April 15, 2011 and is headquartered in New York, NY.                




Chief Technology Officer/Senior Vice President of Product Management

                                    2001 - 2008                


Ziff Davis LLC


                  Ziff Davis LLC operates as a technology, gaming, entertainment and men’s lifestyle firm. It delivers advertising, performance marketing and licensing solutions to clients. The firm’s brands include PGmag.com, IGN, askmen, OOKLA, PC, Salesify, Toolbox.com, and techbargains. The company is headquartered in New York, NY.                




Director of Operations

                                    1998 - 2000                


Juno Online Services, Inc.


                  Juno is an Internet service provider based in the United States. It is a subsidiary of United Online, which also owns NetZero and Kmart's BlueLight Internet service.                




Chief Technology Officer & Senior Vice President-Product Management

                                    Prior                


Ziff Davis Media, Inc.


                  Ziff Davis Media is a leading digital media company specializing in the technology market. One of the first tech media publishing companies to build and grow dedicated, digital businesses, Ziff Davis Media is a name trusted by an ever-growing population of unique online visitors. In the United States, they are most recognized by their award-winning online technology network, the PCMag Digital Network. Ziff Davis Media also has a strong international presence, with brands represented in 45 countries and in 17 languages.They distinguish them selves from its competitors through comprehensive evaluations of the newest and hottest products in The PCMag Labs, as well as through its relationships with recognized industry experts and the thought-provoking reviews, opinions and insights of its editors. Ziff Davis Media's sites are the first stop for many consumers and imminent buyers searching for trusted buying advice. They provide its well-educated, influential buying audience with the information they need to make important purchasing decisions. Reaching more than 30 million tech buyers, visitors and attendees, Ziff Davis Media provides total market coverage of SMB/consumer technology enthusiasts through its portfolio of award-winning brands. At the same time, its advanced online contextual marketing solutions enable marketers to more easily target imminent technology buyers and achieve significantly higher response.Ziff Davis Media has offices in New York City and San Francisco.                




Head-Product

                                    Prior                


Next Issue Media LLC


                  Next Issue Media LLC provides online magazine services. The firm’s offerings are the Next Issue apps for iPad and iPhone, Android and Windows 8 PCs and tablets, which bring magazines to life with digital-only extras such as videos, bonus photography, interactive features, live web links and more. Its tablet technology creates a simplified user experience, allowing readers to focus on the content and immerse themselves with magazine brands they love and catalog includes better homes and gardens, car and driver, esquire, fortune, glamour, GQ, parents, popular mechanics, people, and sports illustrated. The company was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Menlo Park, CA.                




